# {{ project_name }} — backend (FastAPI)

Async FastAPI service with a layered architecture (router → service → repository → model),
async SQLAlchemy 2.0, Alembic migrations, and Postgres.

## Run

From the repo root, the easiest path is Docker (no local Python needed):

```bash
docker compose up --build        # starts db + backend + frontend
```

Native local dev (requires Python 3.11+ and a running Postgres):

```bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e '.[dev]'
alembic upgrade head             # create the schema
uvicorn app.main:app --reload    # http://localhost:8000  (docs at /docs)
```

## Test, lint, type-check

```bash
pytest                           # uses an in-memory SQLite DB — no Postgres required
ruff check . && ruff format .
mypy app
```

## Migrations

```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add x"   # after changing a model
alembic upgrade head                          # apply
alembic downgrade -1                          # roll back one
```

## Layout

```
app/
  main.py            # app factory + router wiring
  core/config.py     # settings (env-driven)
  db/                # engine, session dependency, declarative base
  models/            # ORM models
  schemas/           # Pydantic request/response models
  repositories/      # data access (SQL only)
  services/          # business logic (domain errors)
  api/deps.py        # dependency injection
  api/routes/        # thin HTTP routers
alembic/             # migration environment + versions
tests/               # pytest-asyncio suite
```

To add a resource, copy the `item` files across each layer, wire the router in `app/main.py`,
then generate a migration. See `.claude/rules/fastapi-patterns.md` for the full recipe.
